	</script><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td>
      <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
        <tr>
          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Fun Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Breaking Waves</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><table width='92' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='0'><tr><td background='/magination/gfx/5star.gif'><img src='/lotr/gfx/trans.gif' width='1' height='25'></td></tr></table><font size=1>(4.59)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=29032">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=10347">Daniel "Dartax" Burke</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=10347&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> I&#39;ve always wondered about using an eight energy Orothe creature, so this deck uses Karse and Quilla to try and field some. Aula, Mindseeker, attempts to set the hand up for them. It is a fun deck that uses a lot of Orothe rares.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> May 29, 2003</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Magi:<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(526)">Aula</a>, Mindseeker<br />
(Starting: <a href="javascript:card_browser(454)">Orothean Belt</a>, <a href="javascript:card_browser(461)">Typhoon</a>)<br />
<br />
Karse<br />
(Starting: None)<br />
<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(625)">Quilla</a><br />
(Starting: any two Orothe relics)<br />
<br />
Creatures:<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(431)">C<a href="javascript:card_browser(344)">Ora</a>l Hyren</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(762)">Deep Barl</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(620)">Phrup</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(621)">Reef Hyren</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(622)">Sarazen Guard</a> x3<br />
Sarazen Keeper x3<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(441)">Sea Barl</a> x3<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(443)">Wellisk</a> x2<br />
<br />
Spells:<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(457)">Entangle</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(459)">Submerge</a> x3<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(460)">Tidal Wave</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(461)">Typhoon</a> x3<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(462)">Undertow</a> x2<br />
<br />
Relics:<br />
Hubdra&#8217;s Chest x1<br />
Hubdra&#8217;s Cube x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(628}<a href="javascript:card_browser({435)">Karak</a> Band</a> x1<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(770}<a href="javascript:card_browser({435)">Karak</a> Necklace</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(449)">Orlon</a>&#8217;s Ring x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(454)">Orothean Belt</a> x1<br />
<br />
Total: 40 Cards   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This is not my normal Orothe deck, so I opted to post it. Normally, I use the Abaquist and such, or interchange. This deck was built so I could give Orlons Ring a test run. That alone meant this deck had to be different than my standard control deck. Though, I left in the two Karak Necklace for the cube, and for an opposing control deck (do you think I want to let someone else use my creatures?). <br />
<br />
So far, the deck doesnt seem to start working with Aula, Mindseeker or Karse. There is a decent selection of card draw, but it just doesnt want to show up until Quilla takes the field. It could be my luck, or it could be the deck. Adding Tradewinds would shutoff Orlons Ring, so that is out of the question. However, on the positive side, Quilla has taken out three opposing magi, and faired modestly well when being tag-teamed in a multi-player game. Plus, it almost starts working with Aula, Mindseeker. Now, thats a scary thought, since the deck is designed to actually play the expensive eight energy cards, and she has a base energize of four. <br />
<br />
Aula, Mindseeker. As I was writing this, I wondered if shell start the deck better if I dont retrieve the Orothean Belt among her starting cards. Its still a useful relic for the deck. Yet, if it means a better chance at card draw, it should be well worth the wait. Mostly, you want to draw as much as possible with this magi. If you get Orlons Ring, set out some relics. This will give Aula some extra energy to work with, and if you manage to place Hubdras Chest out as well, these relics may follow you through the magi. <br />
<br />
Well, I was hoping that the deck could use Karse and his savings on the Typhoon and the Sarazen Guard. This actually took place in only one game, but they didnt let him stay long. And, as I said, the card draw doesnt seem to like showing up until Quilla hits the field. So, in theory, if the card draw would happen a bit sooner, he should do quite well. <br />
<br />
Quilla seems to be the powerhouse for this deck. If you dont have any relics in your hand, or in play, then choose your two relics according to what the opponent has. Karak Necklace combined with Hubdras Cube can net you two cards, which is very helpful. When the opponent hasnt left any relics in play for you to borrow (you shouldnt plan on keeping them), then Quilla will probably want to start with Orlons Ring and Orothean Belt. However, it is entirely possible that your relics stayed in play wandering down through the magi thanks to Hubdras Chest. <br />
<br />
Okay, Orlons Ring has purity, just like the relics from the Naroom, Cald, Core, Arderial, and Underneath Leagues. So, if there are only Orothe spells in the discard pile (Aula should put one Typhoon there on your first turn), discard all of your non-Orothe cards from play and add energy to your magi equal to the number of Orothe Relics you control. Hmmm. This is the reason for no Universal relics as well. Although they wont interrupt purity from happening, purity will discard them from play. While there are only nine relics in the deck, it shouldnt be too hard to expand six wide. Though, it will probably be more common to see five of your relics in play at any given time. <br />
<br />
Now, in playtesting thus far, Quilla has averaged an energy gain of twelve per turn, gaining five from the ring in addition to her base energize of seven. This is what got me tag-teamed in that multi-player game. And, Ive sat on the other side of it as well, since I lent the deck to another player so I could test some mods to my decks. It was ugly. My other deck stood up to Quilla as long as it could, but it couldnt just get at that five extra energy she gained at the end of each turn (and all of my Beam of Lights had been used by this point). So, once it lost momentum, Quilla swept through the last two magi rather quickly. <br />
<br />
While this deck isnt meant to be a serious tournament deck (although it does use an extreme amount of rares), it has been able to do one thing fun. Your opponents may just stop playing relics altogether (insert massive grin here). Orlons Ring discards all the non-Orothe cards you control from play, so it can actually reset Hubdras Cube. With Karak Band, this could be two more energy, though its more likely to have the Karak Necklace in play and draw two cards. Either way, it can help you, get rid of their relic, and the cube stays in play to be used again and again and.... Well, you get the picture. Most opponents will learn fast, or regret it. <br />
<br />
As for the rest of the deck, draw cards, discard energy (Typhoon and Reef Hyren), just generally disrupt things (Phrup, Wellisk, and Reef Hyren), and add energy (Submerging a Coral Hyren is fun). And, play a few modest sized creatures without a second thought. <br />
<br />
Now, an interesting challenge. How to suggest alternates for some of the rare/limited cards and keep some of the fun of this deck? Heres some of my ideas. <br />
<br />
Aula, Mindseeker  Orlon (Starting: Sea Barl, Submerge) <br />
Coral Hyren  Sylorum <br />
Deep Barl  Bubble Xyx <br />
Reef Hyren  Ixmin/Seaweed Lascinth <br />
Sarazen Guard  Cawh* <br />
Sarazen Keeper  Blue Yajo <br />
Entangle  Storm of Fishes/Shell <br />
Typhoon  A third Tidal Wave, maybe Bubble Xyx, or Orothe relic(s) of your choice <br />
(Cataclysm will cancel Orlons Ring, so thats not a real possibility) <br />
Hubdras Cube  Relic Stalker/Crushing Surf <br />
Karak Necklace  Orothean Goggles/Barqua&#39;s Bubble <br />
Orlons Ring  Karak Ink <br />
<br />
*Warning: This really will mess with this deck as well. You cant play Cawh while you have a creature in play, and you cant play creatures while Cawh is in play. Still, you might try using the big beat stick of Orothe, though Megathans (another rare) might be better for this deck. <br />
<br />
[edit]<br />
Aula does start better without pulling the Orothean Belt. You may still get the relic anyways when drawing the rest of the opening hand, but she&#39;ll do better on average if it&#39;s not pulled as a starting card.<br />
<br />
Replacing the two Entangle with Owinda&#39;s Gift is very good, even with errata to the spell. Purity can easily recover the cost.<br />
<br />
I have also very recently learned that this deck can have too much card draw for its own good at times. I played a game where I wasn&#39;t using enough cards, or perhaps Aula held on too long or drew too much, so I came to a point where Quilla ran out of discard pile and deck and had no Orothe spells in the discard pile and could not keep them there to trigger purity. I had to play out as much as many cards per turn as I could to rebuild the deck and discard piles. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magination/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=29032"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=29032" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magination/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table></td>
